<subSubSection pageId="10" pageNumber="448" type="multiple">
<paragraph blockId="10.[151,1436,1592,1727]" pageId="10" pageNumber="448">
*1. 
<taxonomicName authority="Shinji 1935" authorityName="Shinji" authorityYear="1935" box="[193,554,1592,1619]" class="Insecta" family="Coccidae" genus="Pulvinaria" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="448" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="katsurae">
<emphasis box="[193,416,1592,1618]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="448">Pulvinaria katsurae</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Shinji, O." box="[424,554,1592,1619]" pageId="10" pageNumber="448" pagination="767 - 777" refId="ref11263" refString="Shinji, O. (1935) A list of the unarmed scale insects collected in the Prefecture of Iwate, with the descriptions of 7 new species. Journal of the Zoological Society of Japan, 47, 767 - 777." type="journal article" year="1935">Shinji 1935</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authority="Ben-Dov, 1993" authorityName="Ben-Dov" authorityYear="1993" box="[609,984,1592,1618]" class="Insecta" family="Coccidae" genus="Pulvinaria" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="448" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="shinjii">
<emphasis box="[609,806,1592,1618]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="448">Pulvinaria shinjii</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Ben-Dov, Y." box="[813,984,1592,1618]" pageId="10" pageNumber="448" refId="ref9966" refString="Ben-Dov, Y. (1993) A Systematic Catalogue of the Soft Scale Insects of the World (Homoptera: Coccoidea: Coccidae). Sandhill Crane Press, Gainesville, Florida, 536 pp." type="book" year="1993">Ben-Dov, 1993</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
(= 
<taxonomicName authority="Shinji 1935" authorityName="Shinji" authorityYear="1935" box="[1024,1295,1592,1619]" class="Insecta" family="Coccidae" genus="Pulvinaria" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="448" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="acericola">
<emphasis box="[1024,1158,1592,1618]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="448">P. acericola</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Shinji, O." box="[1165,1295,1592,1619]" pageId="10" pageNumber="448" pagination="767 - 777" refId="ref11263" refString="Shinji, O. (1935) A list of the unarmed scale insects collected in the Prefecture of Iwate, with the descriptions of 7 new species. Journal of the Zoological Society of Japan, 47, 767 - 777." type="journal article" year="1935">Shinji 1935</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
(nec (Walsh &amp; Riley 1868)) were described from 
<collectingCountry box="[580,644,1628,1654]" name="Japan" pageId="10" pageNumber="448">Japan</collectingCountry>
by 
<bibRefCitation author="Shinji, O." box="[691,845,1628,1655]" pageId="10" pageNumber="448" pagination="767 - 777" refId="ref11263" refString="Shinji, O. (1935) A list of the unarmed scale insects collected in the Prefecture of Iwate, with the descriptions of 7 new species. Journal of the Zoological Society of Japan, 47, 767 - 777." type="journal article" year="1935">Shinji (1935)</bibRefCitation>
. However, morphological information on these two species is quite limited, and 
<bibRefCitation author="Shinji, O." box="[465,631,1664,1691]" pageId="10" pageNumber="448" pagination="767 - 777" refId="ref11263" refString="Shinji, O. (1935) A list of the unarmed scale insects collected in the Prefecture of Iwate, with the descriptions of 7 new species. Journal of the Zoological Society of Japan, 47, 767 - 777." type="journal article" year="1935">Shinji’s (1935)</bibRefCitation>
sets of original 
<typeStatus box="[809,857,1664,1690]" pageId="10" pageNumber="448">type</typeStatus>
material has not been available (probably they have been lost). We therefore did not include these two species in the key.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="10.[151,1437,1772,1942]" pageId="10" pageNumber="448">
*2. The three species of Japanese 
<taxonomicName box="[537,657,1772,1798]" class="Insecta" family="Coccidae" genus="Pulvinaria" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="448" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[537,657,1772,1798]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="448">Pulvinaria</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authority="Shinji 1935" authorityName="Shinji" authorityYear="1935" box="[672,1037,1772,1799]" class="Insecta" family="Coccidae" genus="Pulvinaria" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="448" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="euonymi">
<emphasis box="[672,895,1772,1798]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="448">Pulvinaria euonymi</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Shinji, O." box="[903,1037,1772,1799]" pageId="10" pageNumber="448" pagination="767 - 777" refId="ref11263" refString="Shinji, O. (1935) A list of the unarmed scale insects collected in the Prefecture of Iwate, with the descriptions of 7 new species. Journal of the Zoological Society of Japan, 47, 767 - 777." type="journal article" year="1935">Shinji 1935</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authority="Kuwana 1902" authorityName="Kuwana" authorityYear="1902" box="[1049,1432,1772,1798]" class="Insecta" family="Coccidae" genus="Pulvinaria" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="448" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="oyamae">
<emphasis box="[1049,1264,1772,1798]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="448">Pulvinaria oyamae</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Kuwana, S. I." box="[1272,1432,1772,1798]" pageId="10" pageNumber="448" pagination="43 - 98" refId="ref10918" refString="Kuwana, S. I. (1902) Coccidae (scale insects) of Japan. Proceedings of the California Academy of Sciences, 3, 43 - 98." type="journal article" year="1902">Kuwana 1902</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, and 
<taxonomicName authority="Linnaeus 1758" authorityName="Linnaeus" authorityYear="1758" box="[200,552,1808,1835]" class="Insecta" family="Coccidae" genus="Pulvinaria" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="448" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="vitis">
<emphasis box="[200,374,1808,1834]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="448">Pulvinaria vitis</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Linnaeus, C." box="[382,552,1808,1835]" pageId="10" pageNumber="448" refId="ref11102" refString="Linnaeus, C. (1758) Systema Naturae, per Classes, Ordines, Genera, Species cum Characteribus, Differentii, Synonymis, Locis. Tomus I. Edition X. Reformata. Laurentii Salvii, Holmiae, 823 pp. [in Latin] https: // doi. org / 10.5962 / bhl. title. 542" type="book" year="1758">Linnaeus 1758</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, are very similar to each other, and morphological character states that clearly distinguish them have not been found. On the other hand, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Linnaeus" authorityYear="1758" box="[806,881,1845,1870]" class="Insecta" family="Coccidae" genus="Pulvinaria" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="448" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="vitis">
<emphasis box="[806,881,1845,1870]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="448">P. vitis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is likely to contain several cryptic species, and it would be unwise to treat all of them as one species. For this reason, these three species were included in the 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Linnaeus" authorityYear="1758" box="[1362,1437,1881,1906]" class="Insecta" family="Coccidae" genus="Pulvinaria" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="448" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="vitis">
<emphasis box="[1362,1437,1881,1906]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="448">P. vitis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species group in the key.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
